< review>
We've been coming back to this beautiful beach on the Merced river for years. In the summer it's always refreshing to dip in the water and enjoy the sandy beach.
This time, we happened to come after the first winter snow and the beauty looks very different.< /review>

<Rating>5< /Rating><review>This is a very nice place to go. It's by a river and the river is leach free. The water current is very strong near the middle, so be careful when you go far. There is a campsite near by too, but we didn't do that. There is nice sand and it was very tranquil, especially when it is pretty close to empty. The parking lot was a little hard, especially when there was a truck picking up rafts. It was very nice and I think you would enjoy it.<//review>< pics>

< text>
Cho Dang is a cute and cozy Korean restaurant decorated with calligraphy wallpaper and traditional Korean accessories. Love the Korean flair here.  We went during off hours, and there was a steady stream of diners.

SERVICE: average, needed to reminders to refill water, tea, and banchan

BANCHAN: ~ 6 refreshing dish and fried fish

BIBIMBOP COMBO WITH TOFU SOUP ($16.99): authentic flavor and enough for 2 meals, add you own sauce

SPICY PORK BULGOGI: too spicy for me to handle

GALBITANG ($11.99): nice comfort soup

GINSENG CHICKEN SOUP ($13.99): comfort soup that may need additional salt to flavor accordingly to individual taste

Overall about 3.5 stars, but bump up to 4 for the cute setting< /text>

<Name>Kelvin Ofula<//Name><time>1616566354173<//time>< rating>
5</rating>
<Text>Named after the 1906 earthquake in San Francisco. This place is amazing. Stayed there for a week and enjoyed every single bit of it. The rooms are pretty compact but still managed to put everything essential. Was disappointed that we were sharing bathrooms but that wasn't a big deal at all. They were always clean and very well maintained. The breakfast they provided was equally great with a wide variety of options. They have a public area in the back where you can chill and read or just have a drink. This is a classic example of how you can utilize space. Perfectly decorated and nearly maintained. And it's location is very strategic. Close to many of San Francisco's tourist attractions. Great value for your money I totally recommend it.<//Text>< pictures>

<name>Steven Hull< /name>< date>
1512118908169< /date>
<rate>4<//rate><review>Going in, my main concern was how the shared restroom and shower would end up working out. The answer was no problem at all... A little further walk than normal during the night to empty the bladder, which was compounded by the fact I was at the complete opposite end of the building, but otherwise the no-frills hotel/b and b/dorm was clean, the bed was comfy, the staff was exceptional, and the location was a half block to the BART station with many restaurants either walkable or a stop or two max in either direction. This is definitely a neighborhood in transition, but I never felt unsafe as I have in the meat-packing district. The 'druggies' on the street outside noted by other reviewers are just pot-smoking homeless (as best I could tell) and not once did they accost me for money which was a welcome change from Dallas homeless. I can't say I noticed any noise from outside that would have disturbed my sleep, and my room faced Mission Street. Breakfast had decent selection of bagels, muffins, cereals, and fruits with juice selections and milk. All tasted fresh and great. It wasn't a problem during my stay but there are no individual thermostat controls in the room. The ones in the hallway were locked at 72 F and they provided a small fan/heater in the rooms, but no ceiling fan if it got too warm (72 is perfect for me though). As the ad and reviews mention there is no elevator, so definitely avoid it if you are disabled or elderly. The stairs are fairly steep and the hotel is on the 2nd and 3rd floors of the renovated building.< /review>< Pics>
None<//Pics>

< Text>
I stayed for 4 nights and really enjoyed it. My room was small as youd expect for this price, but it was bright and pleasant and nicely decorated, and plenty of space to hang clothes and put things away. Very quiet too; I never heard any slamming doors or noise from other guests. The shared bathrooms and shower rooms were very clean and well-maintained, and they supply each guest with a bathrobe and slippers. The bed was very comfy and the linens were spotless. I would stay there again and would recommend it to friends.< /Text>

< review>
I had a very enjoyable stay at 1906 Mission. Access to their location by public transit was really easy and convent from the airport and I had no problem getting around San Francisco without a car as I explored the city. The rooms, while small, were very well kept and the shared bathroom facilities for very well managed and clean. All of the front desk staff were very friendly and helped point me in the right direction if I was looking for something to do or seeking service providers for things like laundry. I would definitely stay again and recommend it to anyone wishing to stay in the Mission district.< /review>

< review>
I never stay in hostels but this place was awesome. Very modern, comfortable rooms. The breakfasts were light but really good. The location is great - one block from the BART station so easy access from SFO. The neighbourhood can be a bit dodgy (especially at night) but its cool to be in a less touristy locals hood, close to great coffee shops/restaurants plus all the street art. Never had issues or to wait for the restrooms/showers. The shower rooms are very comfortable! I would definitely stay here again my next visit to SF.<//review>

<user_name>Edmund Hunt< /user_name><Pics>None<//Pics>< text>
I do not believe this places merits all the 5 star reviews it gets. Here I am redressing the balance a little. For the price charged, you could stay in a real hotel (with private bathroom). Realistically, it could be better described as a hostel with not much space, either in the dormitory-style rooms or the dining area. Expect to potentially walk several doors down a corridor to reach the bathroom. Before you pay for a room here, check what alternatives there are and whether you're really getting value for money. If you haven't been to San Francisco before, also bear in mind there are a lot of homeless on the streets in this area.<//text>

This is my second visit to this nail salon. They really did a great job with my mani and pedi! Probably the best I ever had.

The only con I have is that I was really interested in getting a full set of nails but when I mentioned it, I was persuaded not to get them because it was 6 and they were closing in an hour. I think I got there with more than enough time and there was only 1 other person there so I don't know what the problem was. So I didn't do it. HOWEVER, as they were finishing up my manicure, 2 girls walked in, right at 7pm (closing time), asking for full sets and they accepted them! I was appalled and felt completely disregarded.

I'm going to try it one more time and see what happens.</Review>

<GmapID>0x80c32df024a806e9:0xf6cb6453dbc74e5c<//GmapID><Date>1555121656721< /Date>< review>
This is a good place if you are looking for something decent and not too expensive.
Pros: 1) usually not a long wait as place is kinda hidden 2) the two ladies that did my manicure and pedicure took their time, did not rush and made sure my nails disnt come out sloppy looking
3) they accept debit and credit cards $1 fee for that though
4) decent prices
5) no cuts on me thank God
6) good massaging

Cons: 1) a little of a language barrier. It was a little hard to understand certain things . Ended up saying yes to a scrub I didnt know I was being offered so i had to pay extra for that
2) they can be a little harsher than other places when it comes to scrubbing the callouses and dry skin of your feet. They also do not put lotion onto the feet themselves, leaving the feet still looking dry and cracked.
3)they do not give u those little sandals after pedicures or at least not to me. I took close toed shoes and had to walk carefully because the nail polish still felt tacky at the end.
4) they do not put the plastic covers on the things where your feet go therefore you could catch something id they do not disinfect it properly

Overall I would probably come back again :)
UPDATE: hasn't been 24 hrs and I'm already noticing the nail polish wear off at the tips üòÇ and its gel.... *sigh*<//review>

This review is not about those experiences. This review is about today, when I took my Civic in for an alignment. While I waited I spent about an hour wandering the lot and looking at cars during which not a single salesperson could be bothered to come out and say hi. So instead I wandered the other dealers of the auto plaza and discovered some very nice cars and salespeeps at VW, GM, and Hyundai. Several hours after dropping my car off I got a message from Service that my car was done. So I hustled my way back, hopped in and drove off... to discover about 5 minutes later on I-14 at 73 MPH that they hadn't bothered to latch the hood. < Text>
LIARS!  SCAMMERS!
I'm mechanically inclined but was out of town and my family needed the car ASAP. Luckily a credible Honda dealer and a staple of the Antelope Valley was close so I had my 2011 Honda Civic CNG towed to Robertson's Palmdale Honda service department. After assessing the issue, the service advisor calls to give me the bad news...$1,500 to fix the primary issue PLUS... I have a laundry list of items also needing repair. My main concern was getting the car operational so we focused on the primary issue. Being very knowledgeable about the vehicle and knowing what she was saying was not possible, I asked some clarifying questions. Her answers were being formulated as she talked and it was clear, to me, she had no clue what she was talking about and was making it up as she went. I asked if she was familiar with this type of Honda Civic (CNG variant) because the part she claimed had a "hairline" crack was a solid, heavy metal, filter housing. For that to have a crack, hairline or otherwise would indicate a  catastrophic pressure blow out. She admitted that she was basing this on what the Service Technician told her. She asked if I wanted to speak with the Technician but then stated she would text me a video of the damaged part. Unfortunately the video was so grainy I couldn't even make out I was looking at A car much less my car. So I had it towed back home, seriously contemplating getting rid of it all together.
Today I get back in town and the first thing I do is jack up my car to see the part in question for myself. "Hairline " crack?!.. Absolutley Not. Couldn't farther from the truth. The issue... a rubber O-ring failed and needed replacing. I had a few on hand from previous filter replacements, I removed the failed O-ring, lubed the new O-ring with silicone spray, installed and guess what.... repair complete. $1,500?! Suuuuure, if you say so. Took me longer to jack up and secure the car than it took me to replace the O-ring. Any Credibility Roberson's Honda had with me or my family is gone. I can only imagine the scores of unsuspecting local residents Robertson's Palmdale Honda has knowingly taken advantage of. Squandering their Name and credibility for the sake of profit. This company is dead to me, I will never do business with them ever again and everyone I know will know my personal opinion that Robertson's Palmdale Honda is not a trustworthy company. They are LIARS and SCAMMERS. They should refund the $138.00 they charged my daughter for the "assessment" and repay my towing costs for towing the car back home. I welcome any contact from the company<//Text>

I generally hate shopping for a new car. It's a big decision that you need to be good with for X amount of years. Car shopping this time around was made simple at Robertson's Palmdale Honda.  Everyone was extremely friendly, helpful and informative from start to finish.  My sales rep was Mark Neal....He was Incredible! -- answered all my questions, & explained my options.  And if you haven't noticed Honda has changed.  I was returning my 2011 Accord lease and shopping for a new car.  My 2011 drove very well and never gave me any issues, etc, but the new 2014's drive totally different, what major improvements they've made on their already nearly perfect vehicles.  Long story short, I was undecided...did I want a truck, a sedan, a coupe.....I decided on the new Honda Accord Sport and I couldn't be happier!!! < Text>
I have been going here for over 15 years for both sales and service. They have never let me down. I have recommended them to friends and family, including my inlaws. Everyone I've sent to Robertsons has been happy.

The cars I purchased here have been priced fair and have never given me any major mechanical problems. (Knock on wood) The service department has always treated me great and have always been honest and upfront. We even have them work on our other cars that are not Hondas.

Once on a cross country trip my family and I had a problem with one of our vehicles. The dealer in Tennessee wanted to charge us $700 and order a part that would take two days. Robertsons service center diagnosed the problem as a $2 part over the phone! They saved me money and I was back on the road in an hour! The dealership in Tennessee apologized and didn't charge me!

Thank you Robertsons Palmdale Honda!</Text>

Hello Robertson‚Äôs Palmdale Honda-

We just wanted to take the opportunity to thank your dealership, especially Manny Becerra, for the very positive and pleasant shopping experience, with the purchase of a 2021 Honda Accord.

Manny was extremely professional, enthusiastic, and thorough during every stage of the negotiation and presentation of the new vehicle.
Manny definitely understands and exemplifies the motto of the Helpful Honda Sales Professional.

Manny was very professional in the way that he interacted with me and my family. He was very respectful, understanding, and empathetic during the entire process. When he had questions on the payment terms and the extended warranty, he quickly replied to every question and made sure that we understood the answer.

One of the other admirable qualities about Manny is his enthusiasm. He is a great representation of the Honda brand, and is a great advocate for Robertson‚Äôs Palmdale Honda. It was very easy for us to make a connection, because Manny is a lover of rescued and adopted pets.  We have two adopted dogs that are the center of our family, and he shared with us the story and pictures of his lovely adopted dog, which was really cool.

Manny‚Äôs attention to detail was impeccable. He went through literally every feature of the 2021 Honda Accord. There is so much automation on these cars, it is amazing.

Thank you once again for the opportunity to purchase a vehicle in a hassle free environment, and to have a very enthusiastic, thorough, and professional representative like Manny Becerra, made it that much more refreshing and positive.

If you have any questions or would like any additional information regarding my experience, please don‚Äôt hesitate to contact me.

I have always liked this Home Depot; it's clean, convenient, and the staff is so helpful.  After last week, I love this store! < review>
I have always liked this Home Depot; it's clean, convenient, and the staff is so helpful.  After last week, I love this store!  My diamond engagement ring fell out of my purse at Home Depot on Friday.  I talked to the employees and left flyers.  I was fairly certain it was gone forever. On Monday, an employee at Home Depot called me, saying they had found my ring on the floor in the lumber department!
